This paper deals with the de-identification of clinical records using deep learning techniques, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with privacy and security concerns related to sensitive PHI data, which falls under the domain of computer security and cryptography, i.e., cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of deep learning techniques such as BiLSTM-CNN, IDCNN, CRF, BiLSTM-CRF, etc. indicates that the paper also falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper also deals with the efficiency and scalability of the proposed model, which falls under the domain of information retrieval, i.e., cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
